Israeli troops shoot dead a wanted  Moslem fundamentalist and captured four other suspects during a siege in the  mosque massacre town of Hebron on Sunday, military officials said.
One Israeli border policeman was also wounded when he was hit in the head  by a stone during clashes with youths which erupted after the shootout which  lasted several hours.
The troops had been hunting for wanted members of the Islamic Resistance  Movement HAMAS when they came under fire from the house, the officials said.
They surrounded the gang and the militant's body was found in the house,  part of which was destroyed by Israeli firepower.
